 obtain access to OAuth access_token (`grauth` cookie). The vulnerability was fixed by moving from PRNG to `SecureRandom`\n\nThank you, @tomtenisse, for the detailed report and collaboration!","can_view?":true,"can_edit?":false,"content_html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tomtenisse\"\u003e@tomtenisse\u003c/a\u003e identified a vulnerability in Grammarly Keyboard for Android that allowed malicious application installed on the device to guess the PKCE code verifier value and consequently obtain access to OAuth access_token (\u003ccode\u003egrauth\u003c/code\u003e cookie). The vulnerability was fixed by moving from PRNG to \u003ccode\u003eSecureRandom\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThank you, \u003ca href=\"/tomtenisse\"\u003e@tomtenisse\u003c/a\u003e, for the detailed report and collaboration!\u003c/p\u003e\n"},{"category":"researcher","can_view?":true,"can_create?":false}]}